### Remaining Concerns
None structural. The piece is genuinely cohesive — the 5 a.m. / vampirehollie / secret-self thread opens, threads the middle, and lands the ending; "the machine" motif is introduced and paid off consistently; the empathy turn sits at the right pivot. Two boundaries I considered and deliberately left alone:

- **Reading the Comments → drowning/rosie** carries a small time jump ("I hated that about myself" → "fell apart quietly"), but the self-hatred causally sets up the breakdown, so it reads as clear-implicit, not a break.
- **When the Mask Slips** (section 8) could look redundant with the vampirehollie cold open, but it adds new material (Call Her Daddy recoil, derealization) and specifically seeds the ending's "does the real one count as the same person" question — it earns its slot.

Note: this was a scoped cohesion pass only. I did not touch the one open item the second-pass ledger itself flags — only three qualifying testimony quotes (Bruno x2, Amy Allen). A fourth outside voice on the group/comparison dynamic is a content gap, not a cohesion one, so it's out of scope here but worth flagging for whoever does the next content pass.
